      • setHeaders

        public void setHeaders(java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.String> headers)
        Set/override the previously set headers. Note that HTTP headers are case insensitive and thus duplicate header names with only difference being the case will be removed.
        Parameters:
        headers - the map of header names/values, note that the passed list will NOT be used, and an internal copy of the map will be made.
